<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a1df10f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857"><num value="6857">§ 6857.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a1df110-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><chapeau> to the Secretary of the Interior to carry out this chapter—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df111-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/1/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> $2,500,000 for fiscal year 2022; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df112-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/1/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> $5,500,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2025;</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a1df113-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> to the Secretary of Agriculture to carry out this chapter—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df114-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> $2,500,000 for fiscal year 2022; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df115-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> $5,500,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2025; and</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a1df116-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><chapeau> to the Secretary of the Army to carry out this chapter—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df117-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/3/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> $1,500,000 for fiscal year 2022; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a1df118-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6857/3/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> $2,500,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2025.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a1df119-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/114/s8">Pub. L. 117–114, § 8</ref>, <date date="2022-04-29">Apr. 29, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1177">136 Stat. 1177</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
